Development considerations:
- Started with CI/CD to ensure quality gates from the beginning
- GitHub Actions chosen for broad accessibility vs self-hosted runners
- Matrix testing critical given diverse target platforms (Darwin ARM64, Linux ARM64, FreeBSD AMD64, cloud environments)
- Daily scheduled runs catch dependency drift early
- Security scanning integrated to teach secure coding practices

Validation approach:
- Tested workflow syntax with actionlint
- Verified matrix combinations don't explode CI minutes
- Included fail-fast:false to get full platform coverage data

Issues anticipated:
- ARM64 runners might be slower/unavailable
- Windows paths need careful handling
- Docker not available on all platforms (FreeBSD, Replit)
